{
    "name": "1. Solitary Bees",
    "icon": "minecraft:writable_book",
    "category": "productivebees:bees",
    "pages": [
        {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Solitary bees can be found spawning from solitary nests in the overworld. Nests are generated during world gen or can be crafted and placed in the world manually. Each nest will spawn it's own variety of solitary bees and some of them need to be placed in specific biomes. Most solitary bees will not live in hives and do not produce any combs, but they have useful genetics for breeding."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Empty nests will attract a solitary bee after a while as long as the nest is in the correct biome and loaded. Some solitary bees only spawn from the nest of other solitary bees, these are called Cuckoo bees."
        },
